President Trump met with President Ghani of Afghanistan at the Lotte New York Palace Hotel in New York. President Ghani thanked Trump for his decision to increase American troops in Afghanistan, stating that it has made a significant difference on the ground. He also assured Trump that the Afghan people and military will take responsibility for the country's security, with the additional American troops providing assistance and advice. President Trump praised the spirit and determination of the Afghan forces and emphasized the importance of fighting terrorist groups in Afghanistan. He also confirmed that more sanctions will be imposed on North Korea.